Supreme Court of India
Deputy Commissioner Of Sales Tax ... vs Uma Jewellery And Ors. on 11 February, 1981Equivalent citations: AIR 1981 SC 1574, 1981 (1) SCALE 369, 1981 Supp SCC 16, 1981 (13) UJ 187 SC
Bench: A Sen, E Venkataramiah, R Pathak
JUDGMENT
  

1. In all these appeals, the question raised is whether the ornaments and order articles of the Kerala of gold fall within Entry 56 of the First Schedule to the Keraka General Sales Tex Act, 1963. In view of the decision rendered by this Court in Deputy Commissioner of Sales Tex (law) Board of Revenue v. G.S. Pai & Co. , they are liable to be texe at the general rate of 3 per cent under Section 5A read with Section 5(A)(1)(ii) of the Act, That being set aside and the question isa answered in the aforesaid terms. There is no order as to costs.

